<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Speakeasy | Field Guide</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/terminal.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/layout.css">
</head>
<body>

<%- include('partials/header') %>

<div class="guide-page-container">
    <header class="guide-page-header">
        <h1>The Alchemist's Handbook</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">System Architecture & Core Mechanics Spec</p>
    </header>

    <main class="guide-page-content">
        <section class="guide-intro-block">
            <h2>🔬 Core Platform Premise</h2>
            <p>
                This application serves as a computational flavor synthesis engine. Instead of accessing fixed databases, the platform utilizes advanced neural network models to act as a digital mixologist, evaluating the chemical footprints of cataloged reagents—such as pH parameters, solution densities, and solvent properties—to calculate precise molecular beverage protocols.
            </p>
        </section>

        <hr class="guide-divider">

        <h2>🧪 Core Mixology Subsystems</h2>
        <div class="mechanics-stack">

            <div class="mechanic-row">
                <div class="mechanic-meta">
                    <span class="module-tag">Module 01</span>
                    <h3>Stratification Engine</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="mechanic-body">
                    <p><strong>Operational Objective:</strong> Build structurally isolated, multi-layered liquid profiles that resist immediate blending.</p>
                    <p><strong>The Science:</strong> Leverages relative Specific Gravity parameters. Liquid densities are altered dynamically by dissolved carbohydrate mass (sugar concentration measured in Brix) and ethanol scales (ABV). Saturated syrups occupy the foundational layer, while lighter, high-proof spirits are floated sequentially above to control flavor delivery order.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mechanic-row">
                <div class="mechanic-meta">
                    <span class="module-tag">Module 02</span>
                    <h3>Encapsulation Mechanics</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="mechanic-body">
                    <p><strong>Operational Objective:</strong> Suspend target cocktail payloads inside fragile gel membranes that dissolve cleanly on consumption.</p>
                    <p><strong>The Science:</strong> Utilizes direct or reverse polymer cross-linking. Combining a liquid substrate with Sodium Alginate and exposing it to an external Calcium Chloride bath triggers an immediate molecular reaction. Calcium ions displace sodium chains, organizing a flexible hydrogel envelope that isolates the core liquid assets.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mechanic-row">
                <div class="mechanic-meta">
                    <span class="module-tag">Module 03</span>
                    <h3>Acid-Adjustment Pipeline</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="mechanic-body">
                    <p><strong>Operational Objective:</strong> Artificially reconstruct the pH metrics of mild organic inputs to match citrus standards without expanding dilution volume.</p>
                    <p><strong>The Science:</strong> Traditional balancing relies on volatile fruit extractions that alter liquid metrics. By calculating target pH deficits, the engine introduces precise milligram combinations of isolated organic acid powders—Citric, Malic, or Tartaric—directly modifying the acid footprint while keeping volume fluid states constant.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mechanic-row">
                <div class="mechanic-meta">
                    <span class="module-tag">Module 04</span>
                    <h3>Botanical Alchemy</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="mechanic-body">
                    <p><strong>Operational Objective:</strong> Rapidly harvest volatile aromatic compounds and essential oils from dry botanical matrices.</p>
                    <p><strong>The Science:</strong> Eliminates multi-week infusion lag phases by maximizing extraction kinetic efficiency. High-proof neutral grains act as an aggressive polar solvent, targeting the structural cells of root systems, herbs, and spices to rapidly bind volatile essences directly into solution suspensions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </main>
</div>

</body>
</html>